Private-equity firm Advent
International Corp. said it hired banks to arrange debt
financing for its buyout of Mondo Minerals BV from HgCapital.  BNP Paribas Fortis, IKB Deutsche Industriebank AG, and  RBC
Capital Markets  are arranging the senior financing while Ares
Capital Europe Ltd. provided mezzanine debt, Boston-based Advent
said a  statement  today.  Advent said it agreed to buy Amsterdam-based Mondo, the
worldâ€™s second-largest producer of talc, which is used in paper,
